The food it's self is okay, even when they've gotten my order wrong I've let it slide, because the food is good, the delivery man did his part and because after an hour of waiting for my food I was starving - but the customer service experience is atrocious. The men there are very disrespectful and lack any customer service skills.  On may occasions despite being the first customer through the door the guy taking the order would look me over to take the order of the nearest man, even if I was already telling him my order. Again I brushed it off, because the last thing I want is someone hulk spiting in the food that I am ordering for myself and my daughter.  However, this week I've been too ill to cook so I ordered breakfast for my daughter through seemless. Naturally I let her chose where she wanted her food from. But when I ordered (twice) this week the delivery guy made no effort to ring the doorbell (despite having written a request to ring the 1st door bell because my phone is damaged and cannot receive calls). Today after using a neighbors phone to see if the delivery man had passed through (because the delivery guy hadn't  rang the doorbell or passes by in the times that I went down to the front to see if I could catch him when he came to the gate) the manager immediately gave me an attitude when I kindly asked if anyone left to deliver the food yet and reminded him of the special instruction to ring the door bell. He told me to come get the food myself and hung up the phone. Mind you I am very sick, which can be heard by my voice over the phone and the delivery guy was already tipped through the app. On top of that when I checked online for the status of my delivery they claimed that it was already delivered which was clearly incorrect.  It wasn't until my neighbor (a guy) called back the store himself that they agreed to send someone to deliver the food and to be honest I feel a bit offended that it took a man to get them to do their job  and that they even went as far as to pretend there wasn't instructions to ring the doorbell. That's not how you do business. It's misogynistic and disrespectful towards their paying customers.
